"Vinnikov K.Y., Grody N.C.","Global warming trend of mean tropospheric temperature observed by satellites",2003,"Science","302","5643",,"269","272",,,10.1126/science.1087910,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0141993689&partnerID=40&md5=64e6c73346d30660283e0d98f83f2b54","Department of Meteorology, University of Maryland, College Park, MD 20742, United States; Natl. Oceanic and Atmosph. Admin., NESDIS, 5200 Auth Road, Camp Spring, MD 20746, United States","Vinnikov, K.Y., Department of Meteorology, University of Maryland, College Park, MD 20742, United States; Grody, N.C., Natl. Oceanic and Atmosph. Admin., NESDIS, 5200 Auth Road, Camp Spring, MD 20746, United States","We have analyzed the global tropospheric temperature for 1978 to 2002 with the use of passive microwave sounding data from the NOAA series of polar orbiters and the Earth Observing System Aqua satellite. To accurately retrieve the climatic trend, we combined the satellite data with an analytic model of temperature that contains three different time scales: a linear trend and functions that define the seasonal and diurnal cycles. Our analysis shows a trend of +0.22° to 0.26°C per 10 years, consistent with the global warming trend derived from surface meteorological stations.",,"Data reduction; Meteorology; Troposphere; Weather satellites; Diurnal cycles; Global warming; global warming; NOAA satellite; satellite data; temperature; troposphere; accuracy; air temperature; article; circadian rhythm; greenhouse effect; meteorology; microwave radiation; model; priority journal; seasonal variation; telecommunication; troposphere",,,,,,"Spencer, R.W., Christy, J.R., Grody, N.C., (1990) J. Clim., 3, p. 1111; Spencer, R.W., Christy, J.R., (1990) Science, 247, p. 1558; Balling R.C., Jr., Christy, J.R., (1996) J. Geophys. Res., 101, p. 12827; Christy, J.R., Spencer, R.W., Lobl, E.S., (1998) J. Clim., 11, p. 2016; Christy, J.R., Spencer, R.W., Braswell, W.D., (2000) J. Atmos. Ocean. Tech., 17, p. 1153; Christy, J.R., Spencer, R.W., Norris, W.B., Braswell, W.D., (2003) J. Atmos. Ocean. Tech., 20, p. 613; (2000) Reconciling Observations of Global Temperature Change, , National Academies Press, Washington, DC; (2001) Climate Change 2001: The Scientific Basis, , J. T. Houghton et al., Eds. (Cambridge Univ. Press, New York); Manabe, S., Stouffer, R.J., Spelman, M.J., Brian, K., (1991) J. Clim., 4, p. 785; Lanzante, J.R., Klein, S.A., Seidel, D.J., (2003) J. Clim., 16, p. 224; Lanzante, J.R., Klein, S.A., Seidel, D.J., (2003) J. Clim., 16, p. 241; Prabhakara, C., Iacovazzi R., Jr., Yoo, J.-M., Dalu, G., (1998) Geophys. Res. Lett., 11, p. 1927; Wentz, F.J., Schabel, H., (1998) Nature, 394, p. 661; Mears, C.A., Schabel, M.C., Wentz, F.J., (2003) Geophys. Res. Abstr., 5, p. 07241; Santer, B.D., (2003) Science, 300, p. 1280; Vinnikov, K.Y., Robork, A., Cavalieri, D.J., Parkinson, C.L., (2002) Geophys. Res. Lett., 29. , 10.1029/2001Gl014481; Vinnikov, K.Y., Robock, A., Basist, A., (2002) J. Geophys. Res., 107. , 10.1029/2001JD002007; notenoteMo, T., Goldberg, M.D., Crosby, D.S., (2001) J. Geophys. Res., 106, p. 10145; Grody, N.C., (1983) J. Clim. Appl. Meteor., 22, p. 609; Grody, N.C., Zhao, J., Ferraro, R., (2001) J. Geophys. Res., 106, p. 2943; noteIgnatov, A., Laszlo, I., Kidwell, K.B., Goodrum, G., in preparationKarl, T.R., (1993) Bull. Am. Meteorol. Soc., 74, p. 1007; Hansen, J., Ruedy, R., Glascoe, J., Sato, M., (1999) J. Geophys. Res., 104, p. 30997; Hansen, J., Ruedy, R., Sato, M., Lo, K., (2002) Science, 295, p. 275; Jones, P.D., New, M., Parker, D.E., Martin, S., Rigor, I.G., (1999) Rev. Geophys., 37, p. 173; Jones, P.D., Moberg, A., (2003) J. Clim., 16, p. 206; Oort, A.H., Liu, H., (1993) J. Clim., 6, p. 292; Vinnikov, K.Y., Robock, A., Stouffer, R.J., Manabe, S., (1996) Geophys. Res. Lett., 23, p. 1801; note","Vinnikov, K.Y.; Department of Meteorology, University of Maryland, College Park, MD 20742, United States; email: kostya@atmos.umd.edu",,,,,,,,00368075,